INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(28578, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps you can help, $c.', 58158), -- Hero's Call: Eastern Plaguelands!
(28576, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is much to be done here. Both of our enemies are relentless and would slaughter us without mercy the moment we sheathe our blades.', 58158), -- Hero's Call: Western Plaguelands!
(29385, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A small tag on this present reads:$b$bHappy holidays, $n!', 58158), -- A Winter Veil Gift
(26974, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So he\'s really dead? That means...I, Joseph, am the new Scarlet Champion!!!$B$BTake this. I don\'t have a need for such possessions anyways! I\'m the Scarlet Champion, after all.', 58158), -- The False Champion
(26972, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What do you mean Thalnos was an undead? That\'s impossible. The entire mission of the Scarlet Crusade is to destroy the undead! There\'s just no way...$B$BYou have muddied my thoughts. Please take this reward for your achievement and leave me to rest.', 58158), -- The Dark Side of the Light
(29155, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Loot at last!', 55639), -- A Shiny Reward
(25985, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, you were sent here by Tiala? A wonderful student, she\'ll do many great things.$B$BAlthough I sense even greater potential from you.$B$BPlease, stay a while in our shrine. There\'s much to do, but you can\'t accomplish anything with a troubled mind.', 55639), -- Wings Over Mount Hyjal
(27103, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $c, and for that I am forever in your debt.  Though the war is far from over, a great battle has been won against those who would bring about our doom.$B$BPlease - accept this gold as a token of my enduring gratitude.  If we ever cleanse Dire Maul, know that you will be welcomed here as a hero. Thank you.', 55460), -- Shards of the Felvine
(24796, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is nothing short of an amazing accomplishment, $N. The day that Thalorien and Anasterian fell, the same day that Quel\'Delar was lost, was one of the darkest of my life. To see Quel\'Delar restored... it is beyond words.$B$BWithout a doubt, you are meant to be the true bearer of the blade. Quel\'Delar\'s magic is already adapting the blade to your skills and your strengths.', 57359), -- A Victory For The Silver Covenant
(24553, 1, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is unbelievable, $N. You\'ve really done it! All of the quel\'dorei have heard of Thalorien Dawnseeker and Quel\'Delar, but no one ever thought the sword would be restored.', 57359), -- The Purification of Quel'Delar
(24522, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Admit you to the Sunwell? That\'s impossible! The Sunwell is the most sacred and important site of our people. We have only recently reclaimed it with the help of the Shattered Sun Offensive. It is not a place for tourists or travelers.', 57359), -- Journey To The Sunwell
(14443, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Caladis takes the hilt from you and slowly turns it over in his hands.>$B$BThis seems somehow familiar, as though I should know its origins. You say you recovered this in the citadel? Most intriguing.$B$BThere are few who possess the ability to make such a blade. Perhaps they can tell us something about your find.', 57294), -- The Battered Hilt
(28186, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The shackles!  We will begin the process of destroying these shackles immediately $n.  Thank you for your help.', 54901), -- Cursed Shackles
(28185, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Svarnos is finally dead?  Looks like we can finally get to work setting up that cellblock then.  Thank you $n.', 54901), -- Svarnos
(27987, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job on the recovery effort, $n. These cannonballs should last us a while.', 54901), -- Cannonball!
(28046, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s about time someone took those guys out.', 54901), -- Finish The Job
(28050, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No way, you actually killed him?  We are having shark tacos tonight for sure!', 54901), -- Shark Tank
(27944, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work on those spiders, $n.  At this rate, we will be taking that forest in no time.', 54901), -- Thinning the Brood
(28137, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These fish will do nicely, $n.  Keeping the troops fed and in good condition is our number one priority and you really came through for us here.', 54901), -- Teach A Man To Fish.... Or Steal
(28059, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You killed him?  We have been trying to take that guy out for weeks!  We thank you, $n.', 54901), -- Claiming The Keep
(24532, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve got the hang of it.  Go get some practice out there... maybe take out a few of those troggs or trolls.  Or rabbits, I don\'t care.$b$bReturn after you\'ve gotten some practice, and I\'ll show you another trick of the trade.', 54901), -- Evisceratin' the Enemy
(27967, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, you made it back alive!  Can\'t say you were the first one to try this task, but you are definitely the first one to make it back alive.', 54901), -- First Lieutenant Connor
(27991, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha, we finally got Largo!  Nice one, $n.', 54901), -- Taking the Overlook Back
(28130, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Told you that village was full of wackos.  Nice job clearing it out $n.', 54901), -- Not The Friendliest Town
(27970, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it!  Maybe we can finally get some ships into port now.  Thank you $n.', 54901), -- Captain P. Harris
(27864, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No love in your heart for orcs I see. You really made a mess of that guy.', 54851), -- The Crucible of Carnage: The Deadly Dragonmaw!
(28275, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work on those supply ships, $n!  We knew you would be good for somethin\' around here.', 54851), -- Bombs Away!
(27978, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work, $n!  We should not hear from the ghosts again anytime soon.', 54851), -- Ghostbuster
(27966, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I didn\'t think you would be able to do it, $n.  You are just full of surprises aren\'t you?', 54851), -- Salvaging the Remains
(28063, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for rounding these up for us, $n.  Kind of hard to fight a battle without any guns.', 54851), -- Leave No Weapon Behind
(27106, 274, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Samuelson - corrupted by the Twilight\'s Hammer? This must have been going on for years. Right here in my very keep!$B$BI am grateful that you and my son were able to get to the bottom of this before my city was brought to harm. I\'ve underestimated how much Anduin has grown - his command of the holy light just saved my life, if not the entire kingdom.$B$BAs for you - words alone can\'t do justice to your heroism this day. Thank you, $c.', 54737), -- A Villain Unmasked
(27092, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<3 ... 2 ... 1 ...>$B$B<You wet your fingers and snuff out the fuse. The cathedral is saved!>$B$B<Underneath the powder kegs you find a heap of notes and papers. Apparently the cultists were trying to destroy the evidence behind them.>', 54737), -- Cataclysm in the Catacombs
(27072, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You slap Bauden around until he wakes up.>$B$B$C? What are you doing here?$B$BI\'m SI:7 Agent Jack Bauden. This is the longest day of my life.', 54737), -- The Old Barracks
(28807, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Anduin has been investigating the Twilight\'s Hammer? Weren\'t you supposed to keep him OUT of trouble?$B$BHmmm. Let me see those badges you\'ve discovered.', 54737), -- Expert Opinion
(27064, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is REALLY suspicious, $N! Samuelson doesn\'t have a shred of info here about the Twilight Hammer - it\'s almost like he\'s not investigating them. Yet he\'s got a complete catalog of the missing explosives.$B$B<Anduin pulls a medallion from the files.>$B$BAnd I found this funny badge with a symbol on it: A crossed axe and hammer.$B$BIt all means something, but what?', 54737), -- He's Holding Out on Us
(27060, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was a close one! I can\'t believe you stood your ground against so many at once.$B$BIt looks like this site was used for some kind of twisted Twilight\'s Hammer initiation ritual. They\'re definitely active in Stormwind. What\'s this?$B$B<Anduin finds a badge resting on the shrine.>$B$BThis badge shows a crossed axe and hammer. It looks old. If we keep poking around, we might figure out what it means...', 54737), -- Unholy Cow
(27044, 16, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<On seeing the Prince Regent, Farmer Wollerton collapses awkwardly down on one knee.>$B$BY- Y- Your highness!', 54737), -- Peasant Problems
(27038, 1, 5, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Flintlocke greedily digs through the machine parts, tossing choice picks over his shoulder.>$B$BOh aye, \'ere\'s the stuff.$B$B<He sticks his head all the way into one of the crates.>$B$BBut where\'s me powder? Everything\'s here but for the powder. I need explosives, $gman:woman;!$B$BYou tell the King, no powder, no power. I need me some kersplosions or I ain\'t leavin\' port.', 54737), -- Missing Parts
(26975, 2, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Graves bows respectfully to the Prince.>$B$BPlease understand your highness, the men are working double-shifts. The scale of your father\'s operation is enormous.$B$BBut we will endeavor to wrap things up. I give you my word.', 54737), -- Rallying the Fleet
(28295, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Harrison sent you, hmm?$b$bHow fortunate!', 54737), -- Meetup with the Caravan
(28852, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is great news, $N! I\'m glad our drakes were able to assist you. Thank you for rescuing them from the clutches of the Twilight\'s Hammer.', 54737), -- Soften them Up
(27975, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work $n.  I will report your efforts to our highest in command immediately.', 54737), -- WANTED: Foreman Wellson
(27992, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These parts will really help us out, $n!  Who would have thought you can find stuff this useful in all that old junk?', 54737), -- Magnets, How Do They Work?
(27972, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This rum will really help us out, $n.  They might not feel great in the morning but at least they will go to sleep happy.', 54737), -- Boosting Morale
(28163, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those filthy horde never stood a chance.  Nice work, $n.', 54737), -- The Leftovers
(28120, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These journals are in excellent condition $n.  We will begin deciphering them immediately.  Only time will tell what secrets they hold.', 54737), -- Learning From The Past
(28118, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Galus is dead?  Fantastic work $n, now we can send down the cleanup crew and get that cellblock ready for new prisoners.', 54737), -- The Imprisoned Archmage
(28117, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made it back out alive?  You are a stronger man than I, $n.', 54737), -- Clearing the Depths
(28496, 66, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We could sure use some help out here.', 54737), -- Warchief's Command: Azshara!
(29186, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 500, 500, 0, 'So dis is da fetish of da mighty Malacrass? It be a good addition to my collection, $N. And now, I believe, rewards be in order.', 57244), -- The Hex Lord's Fetish
(26862, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. The Molten Elementals\' spirits are finally back to rest.', 56713), -- Elemental Tampering
(29387, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for answering our call for aid, $N.', 56713), -- Guardians of Hyjal: Firelands Invasion!
(29241, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bloodslayer Zala clutches her hand to her chest.>$B$BIt be done, then.  Spilling da blood of our brothers be a grim task.  Da city of da Gurubashi has seen only death an\' hatred for years.$B$BMaybe it be time for da jungle ta retake Zul\'Gurub, an\' wash da scent of death from dis place.$B$BBlood and honor, champion, to da Siame-Quashi you will always be known as \"Bloodslayer\".', 56014), -- Break the Godbreaker
(29242, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What have you got there?$B$BA crazy-looking snake idol?  What am I supposed to do with this?  Hit someone over the head with it and steal something that\'s actually valuable?$B$BThis thing is worthless!$B$B<Briney tosses the Bijou into the water.>$B$BThanks for the \"help,\" I guess.  Here\'s your \"reward.\"$B$BIdiot.', 56014), -- Putting a Price on Priceless
(28223, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, the wardens key\'s.  Another job well done, $n.  These will come in very handy.', 54737), -- The Warden
(28232, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These rations will really help the troops out $n.  Thank you for your help.', 54737), -- Food From Below
(28188, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You cleared that area out?  Looks like you might be more useful to us that we thought, $r.', 54737), -- Prison Revolt
(28162, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like you were able to get the croc hides that we needed.  Thanks $n, your contributions will not go unnoticed.', 54737), -- Swamp Bait
(28165, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'D-Block is all clear?  Good work, $n.  We will send down a crew to start cleaning up right away.', 54737), -- D-Block
(28122, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You actually killed him?!  I can\'t believe it!', 54737), -- A Huge Problem
(25133, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hm... your report comes at a bad time.  The Burning Blade is no longer seen here in Sen\'jin, but we will be vigilant in our efforts to prevent their return to the area.$B$BThe orcs are friends of the Darkspear Trolls.  Honorable friends.  We want to help the orcs, but... we need help too.\n', 54737), -- Report to Sen'jin Village
(25134, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good.  Maybe they\'ll think twice before slacking next time!  Thanks for the help!', 54737), -- Lazy Peons
(25143, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very well.  Now that you know how to speak with the elements, we will test your bond with them.', 54737), -- Primal Strike
(27949, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May their souls rest in peace.', 54737), -- The Forgotten
(78753, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What an interesting find! I will bring this back to $B$BThe Council of Six to investigate further.', 54670), -- Proof of Demise: Threats to Azeroth
(78752, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What evil lies within this!  I will bring this back to $B$BThe Council of Six to investigate further.', 54670), -- Proof of Demise: Titan Rune Protocol Gamma
(25145, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You appear to be a quick learner.', 54647), -- Immolate
(24454, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Caladis accepts the heavy book and begins leafing through it.>$B$BI knew the symbols on the blade were familiar. The weapon was most certainly forged by the dragons and gifted to one of the mortal races, but which blade is this, and how did it come to rest in Icecrown?', 54558), -- Return To Caladis Brightspear
(20438, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew Shandy would find a way to come through for us. Let me get this enchanted and ready for you to use. The sooner you get done with the tabard, the sooner we can get it back to Shandy and the better the chances that its owner will never have missed it.', 54558), -- A Suitable Disguise
(14457, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Arcanist Tybalin examines the captured orders.>$B$BThe agent you intercepted was supposed to transport the Wyrmrest Tome to Icecrown, after meeting with one Magister Hathorel in Sunreaver\'s Sanctuary. We have to get that book, $N, and this is our chance. It\'s not going to be easy, though.', 54558), -- The Sunreaver Plan
(14444, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We can\'t let that book remain in Sunreaver hands. If we hope to identify the sword and use it to our advantage, we have to find a way to capture the book Krasus lent them.', 54558), -- What The Dragons Know
(26204, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work! Keep practicing your charge and you\'ll have an instant advantage at the start of battle.', 54525), -- The Arts of a Warrior
(28174, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you\'re in, then?$b$bGood.', 58158), -- Burning Vengeance
(27567, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see...she did not cooperate. Hopefully we can still stop them before something else terrible happens.', 58158), -- Twilight?! No!
(27565, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t know how I\'m still alive. The patrols keep walking past me like I\'m not even here.$B$B...Am I dead, $c?', 58158), -- Into the Prison
(29838, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, yeah mon! Dat be what I\'m lookin\' for.$b$bHere ya go - take somethin\' nice for your troubles.', 58158), -- One of a Kind
(29840, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You be havin\' my thanks, mon.$B$BThese will be very useful to us, I\'m sure of it.', 58158), -- For Posterity
(29835, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya really did it?$b$bYou surpassed my expectations, mon. Take dis gift for bringin\' justice to da frozen wastes.', 58158), -- Gal'darah Must Pay
(28563, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Heard Westfall was in some deep doody.$B$B<Parker doesn\'t even turn to face you.>$B$BWell, we got our own set of problems here. See them gnolls out there? Looks like they\'re actin\' up again. I don\'t like it. Don\'t like it one bit.', 58158), -- Hero's Call: Redridge Mountains!
(26919, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a quick learner, $N, and the wounded are fortunate to have your aid. Return to me as you grow stronger and I\'ll teach you other spells.', 58158), -- Healing the Wounded
(27067, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have a knack for the healing arts, $N. Wherever you go, your skills as a healer will be in demand. Return to me when you are ready for more training.', 57564), -- Rejuvenating Touch
(27948, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These glands will do nicely.  We are grateful for your help, $n.', 57564), -- A Sticky Task
(27971, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work on the undead up there $n.  We really appreciate the help.', 57564), -- Rattling Their Cages
(27603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Darn it! I simply HAVE to know what\'s behind that gate! This could be the discovery that makes my career, you know!$B$BHmm....maybe a couple good explosions would do the trick...', 56014), -- The Sealed Gate
(29100, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dere ya have it, $n.  It look like we gonna lead an assault on da Gurubashi in Zul\'Gurub.$b$bDese be dire times for us Darkspear.  But dey be even more dire for da Zandalar.  Dey goin\' too far.$b$bYa been good to Bwemba, hopefully ya gonna continue to help out all of Stranglethorn.$b$bSpirits be wit\' ya, $n.', 56014), -- Bwemba's Spirit
(29132, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is no whimsical dalliance that brings you here, mortal.$b$bMuster every fiber of your courage for what you are about to behold.', 56014), -- A Legendary Engagement
(29153, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You killed them all?  I wish that would ease my mind, but these guys seem to have a habit of coming back from the dead.$b$bAh, but what\'s that you have?$b$bYou say it might keep them out of Booty Bay?$b$bNow we are talking!$b$bOh right, I said I had a reward for you?  Sure... Just give me a minute to find it.', 55639), -- Booty Bay's Interests
(29217, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hadn\'t expected to see dem again, $N. The information dey gathered will be da key to destroying Zandalari influence in Zul\'Aman. Ya have my thanks and da thanks of my scouts.', 55639), -- The Captive Scouts
(28512, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well whadda we have here?  You here to help?', 55639), -- To the Aid of the Thorium Brotherhood
(26838, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to our camp, $c.  You couldn\'t have arrived at a better time.', 55262), -- Rebels Without a Clue
(26150, 1, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'William sent you? Bless his soul. I... I\'m ok... It\'s just... Well...', 55141); -- A Visit With Maybell
